comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-07T20:44:47.549Z",codex-agent,"Implementation start: bundled with pm-zwpp, pm-oxrw, pm-m4iu, pm-cbwg, pm-w89s, and pm-usfg. Live duplicate/context check found no closed schema/config/profile SDK primitive completion; prior read/lifecycle/package primitives remain separate shipped or in-progress domains."
  "2026-07-07T22:45:27.701Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: post-review docs/API cleanup keeps package authors on the correct context-management primitive shapes: linked file/doc adds use string arrays and top-level note, while SchemaResult documents the generic schema customization result union. Verified through docs gate, typecheck, focused SDK tests, and packed installed SDK proof."
  "2026-07-07T23:52:21.378Z",claude-code-agent,"Review follow-up evidence: the generic SDK schema() return type now explicitly includes all concrete inspect results as well as schema mutation results, preserving compile-time safety for customization primitive consumers. Focused SDK test and full coverage passed."
  "2026-07-08T00:36:44.011Z",claude-code-agent,"Review follow-up evidence: schemaShow, schemaShowField, schemaShowStatus, profileShow, and profileLint now pass their name positional as a top-level SDK action property, matching the established SDK command wrapper convention used by other positional helpers."
  "2026-07-08T06:06:35.974Z",codex,"Evidence: context-management SDK primitives remain covered by full coverage and installed-package proof; lifecycle shortcuts now expose typed composed result contracts so agent/package authors can consume claim/update/close/release payloads without unknown casts."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T17:32:56.449Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation slicing 2026-07-10 (grounded in current src state). Already public — do NOT redo: profile read-side (presets/plan/describe/lint exported via src/sdk/index.ts), schema runtime registries (resolveRuntimeFieldRegistry/resolveRuntimeStatusRegistry via src/sdk/runtime.ts), and generic PmClient.runTyped wrappers for the schema/config/profile/init actions. The actual gap: domain logic lives in CLI command modules — src/cli/commands/schema.ts (1973 lines), config.ts (1576), init.ts (955) + init-agent-guidance.ts (566), ~5.1k lines total — so SDK consumers reach these domains only through generic action dispatch, not typed primitives. Suggested slices: S1 schema mutation primitives (~150m) — extract add-type/add-field/status-def write paths into src/core/schema (fields-file/item-types-file/status-defs-file already own the file formats); command becomes parse+render. S2 config/settings primitives (~90m) — extract read/write/validate onto src/core/config/nested-settings; preserve the settings validator's unknown-key-stripping semantics (PR#314). S3 init + workspace-discovery primitive (~90m) — single source of truth for discovery; this is where the GH-501/pm-69nl class (init target invisible to discovery) gets fixed at the primitive level — coordinate with pm-69nl, do not duplicate its fix. S4 typed PmClient facades + SDK reference docs/tests (~60m) — replace generic payloads with typed inputs/outputs; each primitive must match the equivalent runAction result shape (semantics oracle, pm-usfg 07-06 note). Order: S1 first (schema gates the pm-w89s universality story); S2/S3 independent; S4 last."
